values.value: Programmed death ligand 1 (PD-L1) is a protein that is found on the surface of many cells. Cancer cells sometimes have large amounts of this protein to help the cancer cells avoid the body’s immune system (your body’s natural defense system). This test measures how much PD-L1 is present on cancer cells. Some types of treatments may be more suitable for you if you have higher levels of PD-L1 present on your cancer cells. This test may help doctors predict which cancer treatments may work for you.
